                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                            <p>قرق وزیر تأريخي</p>
                            <p>An imperfect copy of the well-known Ottoman Turkish version of the
                                History of the Forty Vezirs, made in the 15th century by Aḥmad-i
                                Miṣrí, or Sheykh-záde, which has been translated into English by E.
                                J. W. Gibb. See Rieu, B.M.T.C., pp. 216-219; Flügel, Vienna Cat.,
                                vol. I, p. 417; and cp. Gibb, Hist. of Ottoman Poetry, vol. I, p.
                                430, n. 1, and vol. V, p. 13, n. 1.</p>
                            <p>Begins:</p>
                            <p>حمد و ثنا بی منتها اول بار تعالی حضرتنه</p>
                        </summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="X_9-item1">
                            <author key="person_f8342" cert="medium">
                                <persName xml:lang="ota-Latn-x">Aḥmad-i Miṣrí (Sheykh-záde)</persName>
                            </author>
                            <title xml:lang="tr" key="work_23242">Ḳırḳ Vezír Tarihi</title>
                            <title xml:lang="ota" key="work_23242">قرق وزیر تأريخي</title>
                            <title xml:lang="en" type="desc">History of the Forty Vezirs</title>
                            <note>Imperfect copy. Translated into English by E. J. W. Gibb. See
                                Rieu, B.M.T.C., pp. 216-219; Flügel, Vienna Cat., vol. I, p. 417;
                                and cp. Gibb, Hist. of Ottoman Poetry, vol. I, p. 430, n. 1, and
                                vol. V, p. 13, n. 1.</note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="ota">حمد و ثنا بی منتها اول بار تعالی
                                حضرتنه</incipit>
                            <explicit/>
                            <textLang mainLang="ota">Ottoman Turkish</textLang>
